    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-10-24T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-10-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="328"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3363: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fernald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-24T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >October 24, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Dr. Carlos Calvo is appointed special envoy plenipotentiary leaving 27th for
                    Buenos Aires. Negotiations are very secret, but apparently Argentina and Brazil
                    have made peace proposal following Salamanca telegram of 12th.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d328fn43">In reply to the telegram of the Presidents of Argentina
                        and Brazil of October 11. The telegram in part states that the “Government
                        of Bolivia shares your desires, and is, as always, disposed to consider and
                        accept every project which assures peace on the foundation of justice,
                        conciliating the fundamental interests of two belligerent countries”.
                        (724.3415/3365) The telegrams are printed in Republica de Bolivia,
                        Ministerio de Relaciones Exteriores y Culto, <hi rend="italic">Memoria
                            presentada al Oongreso de 1934, Conflicto del Chaco</hi>, p. 434.</note>
                    Local newspapers hopeful for armistice by November 11th.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fernald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
